1️⃣ What is Amazon CloudWatch?
Amazon CloudWatch is a monitoring and observability service provided by Amazon Web Services (AWS).

It helps you:

1)Monitor AWS resources
2)Monitor applications
3)Collect logs
4)Set alarms
5)Track performance
6)Automatically react to changes

Think of it as:
🧠 “The Health Monitoring System of your AWS Infrastructure”

2️⃣ Why CloudWatch is Important in DevOps?
Build → Deploy → Monitor → Improve

CloudWatch helps in the Monitor phase.

Without monitoring:
You won’t know if server CPU is high
You won’t know if app crashed
You won’t know if traffic suddenly increased
You won’t know if users are facing errors

3️⃣ Core Components of CloudWatch
🔹 A) Metrics
Metrics are numerical data points over time.

Examples:
CPU Utilization
Memory Usage
Disk I/O
Network In/Out
Request Count

Example:
If you are using Amazon EC2,
CloudWatch automatically collects:

CPUUtilization
NetworkIn
NetworkOut
DiskReadOps
DiskWriteOps

🔹 B) Custom Metrics
You can send your own metrics using:

boto3 (like your Flask app)
AWS CLI
SDK
Namespace: OnlineStore
MetricName: PageViews

🔹 C) Logs (CloudWatch Logs)
CloudWatch stores logs from:

EC2
Lambda
ECS
Application logs
System logs

If using
AWS Lambda

Logs automatically go to CloudWatch.


🔹 D) Alarms
Alarms trigger action when condition is met.
CPUUtilization > 40%
for 2 minutes

When triggered:

Send email
Send SMS
Auto scale
Trigger Lambda
Alarms use:

📩 Amazon Simple Notification Service

Service
🔹 E) Dashboards

Dashboards allow:
Custom monitoring screen
Multiple graphs
Multi-service view
Example Dashboard:
EC2 CPU
RDS connections
Lambda errors
API latency


🔹 F) Events (Now EventBridge)
CloudWatch Events is now:

⚡ Amazon EventBridge

Used for:
Scheduled tasks (cron jobs)
Trigger automation
React to AWS state changes

Example:
When EC2 stops → Send notification.

🔹 G) CloudWatch Agent
By default EC2 collects only basic metrics.

If you want:
Memory usage
Disk space
Custom logs
You must install CloudWatch Agent on EC2.

 CloudWatch vs Grafana
You asked earlier.

CloudWatch:

AWS native
Integrated
Easy

Grafana:

Advanced visualization
Multi-cloud support
Better dashboards

Amazon CloudWatch is a monitoring and observability service in AWS that collects metrics, 
logs, and events, and triggers automated actions using alarms and dashboards.



